Report to Stigma-4.
Analysis indicates that the Grebuloffs continue to abide on Elysion without difficulty. However, data insufficiencies remain regarding the oceans created through their influence on dynamis.
With sufficient data, it will be possible to preserve such ocean environments and improve Grebuloff well-being. Initiating research and analysis protocol...
Samples of limestone coral are required to proceed with analysis. Once procured, please deposit the samples in the analysis unit.
Elysian cucumber samples are required to proceed with analysis. Once procured, please deposit the samples in the analysis unit.
An Elysian nudibranch sample is required to proceed with analysis. Once procured, please deposit the sample in the analysis unit.
For maximum efficiency, use of gold salmon roe is strongly advised. All proceeds go to Omicron enhancement initiatives.

Scanning inventory... Unidentified substances detected. Potential value and utilization factors...unclear.
Standing by for oceanic samples.
Scanning inventory... Oceanic samples detected. Please insert for analysis.
Analyzing... Sample possesses bacteria given to releasing foreign particulates. Olfactory sensors reaching critical.
Conclusion: oceanic life-forms are prone to...unfavorable odor. Additional specimens required for further analysis.
Conclusion: ocean life-forms remain prone to unfavorable odor. Probability of fragrant life unlikely. Additional specimens required for further analysis.
Report from analysis unit received. Your contribution was deemed beneficial to research on Elysion's oceanic environment.
However, data insufficiencies remain. If discovered bacteria is present in all oceanic life-forms, verification of potential dissemination to other non-oceanic hosts is required.

Proposal: submerge the redolent, fluffy manager in ocean water, and monitor odor fluctuations. Upon conclusion of this experiment, deployment of military-grade lasers may be authorized for decontamination purposes.
Periodic analysis of new specimens is required for continued research and environmental preservation. Your future cooperation is greatly appreciated.
